designflow-backend\AGENTS.md:346:**Actually:** `quote_id` (`RFQVendor_id`) is a sequential integer, so a malicious vendor could enumerate other factories' quotes and POST `updateVendor` / `keepPrice` against them (IDOR). The guard blocks the one real case — a `vendor` whose token `factory_id` differs from the quote's `vendor_id_fk` — and deliberately **fails open** for internal roles, vendors with no `factory_id` on their token (legacy records), and quote rows with no `vendor_id_fk`. The intent is to close the enumeration hole without ever locking out a legitimate user (notably the invite-an-individual-vendor-to-one-item flow, where the invited factory owns its own quote row).
